2272. Substring With Largest Variance

The variance of a string is defined as the largest difference between the number of occurrences 
of any 2 characters present in the string. Note the two characters may or may not be the same.
Given a string s consisting of lowercase English letters only, 
return the largest variance possible among all substrings of s.
A substring is a contiguous sequence of characters within a string.

// https://leetcode.com/problems/substring-with-largest-variance/editorial/
+++++rest is IMPORTANT+++++ 

Example 1:

Input: s = "aababbb"
Output: 3
Explanation:
All possible variances along with their respective substrings are listed below:
- Variance 0 for substrings "a", "aa", "ab", "abab", "aababb", "ba", "b", "bb", and "bbb".
- Variance 1 for substrings "aab", "aba", "abb", "aabab", "ababb", "aababbb", and "bab".
- Variance 2 for substrings "aaba", "ababbb", "abbb", and "babb".
- Variance 3 for substring "babbb".
Since the largest possible variance is 3, we return it.

Example 2:

Input: s = "abcde"
Output: 0
Explanation:
No letter occurs more than once in s, so the variance of every substring is 0.

=====Kadane approach=====

class Solution {
    public int largestVariance(String s) {
        int[] freq = new int[26];
        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
            freq[c - 'a']++;
        }
        int result = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < 26; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < 26; j++) {
                if (i == j || freq[i] == 0 || freq[j] == 0) {
                    continue;
                }
                int major = (char)('a' + i);
                int minor = (char)('a' + j);
                int majorcount = 0;
                int minorcount = 0;
                int rest = freq[j];
                for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
                    if (c == major) majorcount++;
                    if (c == minor)  {
                        minorcount++;
                        rest--;
                    }
                    if (minorcount > 0) result = Math.max(result, majorcount - minorcount);
                    if (majorcount < minorcount && rest > 0) {
                        majorcount = 0;
                        minorcount = 0;
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        return result;
    }
}